Solution
Let t = log_2 x, so x = 2^t with t ≠ 0. Then log_4 x = t/2, log_x 16 = 4/t, log_x 8 = 3/t. The equation becomes t/2 - 4/t = 7/6 - 3/t, i.e. t/2 - 1/t - 7/6 = 0. Multiplying by 6t gives 3t^2 - 7t - 6 = 0, with Δ = 121, so t = (7 ± 11)/6 → t = 3 or t = -2/3. Thus x = 2^t ∈ {8, 2^{-2/3}}. Both are valid (x>0, x ≠ 1).

\boxed{ \{8,\; 2^{-2/3}\} }
